access switch target
(a) SSH (Secure Shell)

Used to securely access the device.

Basic Config:
ip domain-name example.com
crypto key generate rsa modulus 2048
ip ssh version 2
line vty 0 15
 login local
 transport input ssh

(b) SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol)

Used for monitoring by tools like SolarWinds, PRTG, Cisco DNAC.

Basic Config:
snmp-server community public RO
snmp-server community private RW

(c) NTP (Network Time Protocol)

Keeps device clock synchronized (important for logs).

Basic Config:
ntp server 10.1.1.1
ntp server 10.1.1.2 prefer

ðŸ”¹ 2. Layer 2 Protocols
(a) STP â€“ Spanning Tree Protocol

Prevents loops in switching network.

Basic Config:
spanning-tree mode rapid-pvst
spanning-tree portfast default
spanning-tree extend system-id

(b) VLAN & Trunking

Segmentation of network.

Basic Config:
vlan 10
 name USERS
vlan 20
 name SERVERS

interface range g1/0/1-48
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 10

interface g1/0/49
 switchport mode trunk
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 10,20

(c) LACP / EtherChannel

Used for bundling ports.

Basic Config:
interface range g1/0/1-2
 channel-group 1 mode active

ðŸ”¹ 3. Layer 3 Protocols
(a) Static Routing
ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 10.1.1.1

(b) Dynamic Routing (OSPF, EIGRP)

Used on L3 switches and routers.

OSPF Basic:
router ospf 1
 network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0

ðŸ”¹ 4. Security Protocols
(a) DHCP Snooping

Protects from rogue DHCP servers.

ip dhcp snooping
ip dhcp snooping vlan 10,20
interface g1/0/48
 ip dhcp snooping trust

(b) Dynamic ARP Inspection (DAI)

Protects against ARP spoofing.

ip arp inspection vlan 10,20
interface g1/0/48
 ip arp inspection trust

(c) Port Security

Used on access ports to limit connected devices.

interface g1/0/10
 switchport mode access
 switchport port-security
 switchport port-security maximum 2
 switchport port-security violation restrict

ðŸ”¹ 5. Monitoring Protocols
(a) NetFlow

Traffic visibility.

flow exporter NetFlow1
 destination 10.1.1.50
 source vlan 10

(b) Syslog

Send logs to a central server.

logging host 10.1.1.20
logging trap warnings

ðŸ”¹ 6. Wireless Controller (Cisco 9800) Specific Protocols
(a) CAPWAP

Used between APs and WLC.
No manual config; AP discovers WLC automatically (DHCP option 43, DNS, or L2 discovery).

(b) RADIUS / TACACS+

Used for user authentication on WiFi.

Example:
aaa new-model
radius server ISE1
 address ipv4 10.5.5.5 auth-port 1812 acct-port 1813
 key C!sco123

ðŸ”¹ 7. High Availability / Redundancy Protocols
(a) HSRP / VRRP

First hop redundancy.

interface vlan 10
 standby 1 ip 10.1.1.1

(b) SSO / StackWise

For switches:

redundancy
 mode sso
